IF STATEMENTS

if() The logical expression inside an if statement will evaluate to either true or false. If it evaluates to true, then the block of code contained in the curly braces following the if statement will print. 

if(5 > 3)
{
 console.log(“hello”); // prints hello because 5 is greater than 3
}

if(5 > 10)
{
  console.log(“goodbye”); // DOESN’T print goodbye because 5 is not greater than 10
}

ELSE will print if the if condition is untrue:

if(1000 < 1)
{
console.log('1000 is less than 1');
}
else
{
console.log('1000 is NOT less than 1');
}